fr.eikasus.objectsmyfriends.model.bo

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.eikasus.objectsmyfriends.model.bo.User
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @Entity
public class User
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Class representing a user.

    This class define a user. Among standard methods like getters and setters or constructors, the class define a useful method to hash the plain password. This method is part of the User class instead of Business Logic Layer because the hashing process is more specific to the class implementation. See hashPassword() for more details.

    See Also:
    hashPassword(), Serialized Form

      • hashPassword

        public void hashPassword()
                  throws ModelException
        Hash the plain password.

        Hash the password for the user. The password need to be present and valide in the object. After the operation, the password is hashed and a salt specific to this user is created. Be aware that after the method succeed, the plain password property of the user is emptied. The user can have an already defined salt. In that case, it is used instead of created again.

        Throws:
        ModelException - In case of error
